modules.description: Provides functions to start and stop profiling sections, record events, and manage trace data using a C API. Works with custom data structures for timestamps, event markers, and trace buffers. Used to instrument performance-critical code paths in game engines or real-time systems for detailed runtime analysis.

Provides functions to create and manage tracing spans, annotate them with text, values, and colors, and control their lifecycle. Works with spans represented as integers and supports adding detailed information like file names, line numbers, and function names. Used to instrument code for performance analysis, track execution flow, and log structured data during runtime.

Provides functions to create and install a trace collector for instrumenting application execution. Works with the `Trace.collector` type to capture and manage tracing data. Used to initialize tracing infrastructure in applications for runtime analysis.
